body:
Hi,

I believe we currently do not support Python2...
Yes, but maybe it can work nevertheless. For installing I had to change <10 lines of code.
We don't plan to support Python 2. Even if it works with < 10 lines of code, we don't want to keep maintaining it. Thanks!
I didn't ask for maintanance, I asked for advice. Whats the problem keeping this issue open for a day or two in case somebody knows how to fix it?

Sure, I was just setting the right expectations. Also, reproducing and debugging unsupported scenarios takes away resources from addressing issues related to supported scenarios. Please feel free to re-open and we'll be more than happy to help as time permits.
I think I cannot reopen because have no permissions.

I experimented with this a bit.
The error you are encountering can be addressed by changing
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/python/version_script.lds#L4
from
PyInit_onnxruntime_pybind11_state;
to
initonnxruntime_pybind11_state;

I assume you made some other minor modifications to build onnxruntime_pybind11_state.so using python 2.7

I didn't test extensively, but I was able to import onnxruntime , load resnet50 model and run an inference successfully with python2.7
adding a reference to https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/2153 in case someone else comes across it.
Marking this as closed. We do not officially support python 2 but you can try the suggested fix above.

issue.title: Cannot install onnxruntime with pip/python2

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
```
$ pip search onnxruntime | head
DEPRECATION: Python 2.7 reached the end of its life on January 1st, 2020. Please upgrade your Python as Python 2.7 is no longer maintained. pip 21.0 will drop support for Python 2.7 in January 2021. More details about Python 2 support in pip can be found at https://pip.pypa.io/en/latest/development/release-process/#python-2-support pip 21.0 will remove support for this functionality.
scikit-onnxruntime (0.2.1.4)  - Scikit-learn wrapper of onnxruntime
onnxruntime-tools (1.4.2)     - Transformers Model Optimization Tool of ONNXRuntime
onnxruntime (1.4.0)           - ONNX Runtime Python bindings
onnxruntime-gpu (1.4.0)       - ONNX Runtime Python bindings
$ pip install onnxruntime
DEPRECATION: Python 2.7 reached the end of its life on January 1st, 2020. Please upgrade your Python as Python 2.7 is no longer maintained. pip 21.0 will drop support for Python 2.7 in January 2021. More details about Python 2 support in pip can be found at https://pip.pypa.io/en/latest/development/release-process/#python-2-support pip 21.0 will remove support for this functionality.
ERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement onnxruntime (from versions: none)
ERROR: No matching distribution found for onnxruntime
$ pip install onnxruntime-gpu
DEPRECATION: Python 2.7 reached the end of its life on January 1st, 2020. Please upgrade your Python as Python 2.7 is no longer maintained. pip 21.0 will drop support for Python 2.7 in January 2021. More details about Python 2 support in pip can be found at https://pip.pypa.io/en/latest/development/release-process/#python-2-support pip 21.0 will remove support for this functionality.
ERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement onnxruntime-gpu (from versions: none)
ERROR: No matching distribution found for onnxruntime-gpu
```



**Describe the bug**
Unable to install onnxruntime with pip on Python2

**Urgency**
urgent for my private project.

**System information**
Ubuntu 16.04
python 2.7
pip 20.2.3

**To Reproduce**
`pip install onnxruntime`

**Expected behavior**
onnxruntime installs

I know python2 is deprecated, but I don't have a choice for the time being, even if this can't be fixed any suggestions on how I might install onnxruntime for python2 would be greatly appreciated.
